questions.statement:
&lt;p&gt;Read the given statements and conclusions carefully. Assuming that the information given in the statements is true, even if it appears to be at variance with commonly known facts, decide which of the given conclusion(s) logically follow(s) from the statements.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Statements:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;All dolls are robots.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Some robots are toys.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Some toys are cycles.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Conclusions:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(I) Some toys are dolls.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(II) No cycle is a robot.&lt;/p&gt;

questions.explanation:
&lt;p&gt;The least possible venn diagram is:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/images/production/quesImages/qImage67e3f97021339e4281440ee5.png&quot; /&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;//storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/25/09/IMG-1198-Arpit-35.png&quot; style=&quot;width: 270px; height: 138px;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Conclusions:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(I) Some toys are dolls&amp;nbsp;&amp;rarr; False ( there is no direct relation between toys and dolls. so, it can be a possibility)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(II) No cycle is a robot&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&amp;rarr;&amp;nbsp;False ( there is no direct relation between cycle and robot. so, it can be a possibility)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;Thus,&amp;nbsp;Neither conclusion (I) nor (II) is true.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hence, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Option 4&amp;quot;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

questions.statement:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Refer to the following number series and answer the question.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;5 3 6 8 2 6 3 2 8 0 3 8 5 6 7 2 5 0 9 6&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;How many such odd numbers are there each of which is immediately preceded by an odd number and immediately followed by an even number?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

questions.explanation:
&lt;p&gt;We have to find the triad which looks like (odd, odd, even) in the given series:&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/images/production/quesImages/qImage15676.png&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We can see that &lt;strong&gt;there is only one such odd number&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;which is immediately preceded by an odd number and immediately followed by an even number.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Hence the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;option 2)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Seven friends K, L, M, N, O, P and Q are sitting on a straight bench facing north.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1) K is sitting exactly at the middle position.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2) L is sitting third to the right of K.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;3) K is sitting to the immediate left of O.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;//storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/22/07/F1_Savita_Railways_04-7-22_D31.png&quot; style=&quot;width: 287px; height: 107px;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;4) Only P is sitting between Q and N.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;5) M and Q are not sitting at any of the extreme ends.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Thus, we can see that Q cannot be sitting at the left end. Therefore, N sits at the left end.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;//storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/22/07/F1_Savita_Railways_04-7-22_D32.png&quot; style=&quot;width: 290px; height: 106px;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;6) Final sitting arrengment is:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;//storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/22/07/F1_Savita_Railways_04-7-22_D33.png&quot; style=&quot;width: 287px; height: 108px;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So,&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;N&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;is sitting at the extreme left end.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Hence, the correct answer is&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;quot;N&amp;quot;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

questions.statement:
&lt;p&gt;Select the set in which the numbers are NOT related in the same way as are the numbers of the following sets.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(192, 12, 10),(195, 15, 7)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(NOTE: Operations should be performed on the whole numbers, without breaking down the numbers into its constituent digits.)&lt;/p&gt;

questions.explanation:
&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;The logic followed here is:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;Logic: &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;(1st number &amp;divide; 2nd number) - 6 = 3rd number&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;Now,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;For, 192 : 12 : 10&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; (192 &amp;divide; 12) - 6 = 16 - 6 = 10.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;For, 195 : 15 : 7&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&amp;rArr; (195 &amp;divide; 15) - 6 = 13 - 6 = 7.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;Similarly, for&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: var(--bs-body-font-family); font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;208 : 13 : 16&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;rArr; (208 &amp;divide; 13) - 6 =&amp;nbsp;16 - 6 &amp;ne;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;10&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;Hence, the correct answer is &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;Option 1&amp;quot;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/mistake-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Mistake Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;The question is asking about not Similar, so mark that option which is not similar to given set.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;BODMAS Rule:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;Bodmas Rule MCQ [Free PDF] - Objective Question Answer for Bodmas Rule Quiz  - Download Now!&quot; src=&quot;//storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/23/11/6203fea433474e3b330f0951_22-7-22_Shashi%20Savita_D1.png&quot; style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; width: 368px; height: 193px;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Lets check each option:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div&gt;1) + and -&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;After interchanging signs, we get:&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;rArr; 97 &amp;times; 23 +18 - &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;9 &amp;divide; 3&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;rArr; &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;97 &amp;times; 23&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt; + 18 - 3&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;rArr; &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;2231 + 23&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt; - 3&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;rArr; &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;2254 - 3&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;rArr; &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;2251 &amp;ne; 66&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;2) &amp;times; and &amp;divide;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;After interchanging signs, we get:&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;rArr; &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;97 &amp;divide; 23&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt; - 18 + 9 &amp;times; 3&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;rArr; 4.217 - 18 + &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;9 &amp;times; 3&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;rArr; 4.217 - &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;18 + 27&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;rArr; &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;4.217 - 45&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;rArr;&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;40.783 &amp;ne; 66&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;3) &amp;times; and +&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;After interchanging signs, we get:&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;rArr;97 +&amp;nbsp;23 -&amp;nbsp;18 &amp;times;&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;9 &amp;divide; 3&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;rArr; 97 + 23 - &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;18 &amp;times; 3&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;rArr; &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;97 + 23&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt; - 54&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;rArr; &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;120 - 54&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;rArr; &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;66 = 66&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;4) &amp;divide; and -&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;After interchanging signs, we get:&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;rArr;97 &amp;times; &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;23 &amp;divide; 18 &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;+ 9 - 3&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;rArr; &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;97 &amp;times; 1.27&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt; + 9 - 3&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;rArr; &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;123.94 + 9&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt; - 3&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;rArr; &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;132.94 - 3&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;rArr; &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;129.94 &amp;ne; 66&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;Hence, &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;option 3&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; is the correct answer.&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The pattern followed here is:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;//storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/22/07/F3_Madhuri_SSC_22.07.2022_D2.png&quot; style=&quot;width: 282px; height: 73px;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hence, the correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;6&amp;quot;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Logic followed here is:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;First number &amp;times; 11 = Second number&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Check each option,&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

