&lt;p&gt;Given that:-&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Only one person is &lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;younger&lt;/span&gt; than Y.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Y &amp;gt; _ .&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;X is older than E but younger than D.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;D &amp;gt; X &amp;gt; E&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;E is older than Y.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;E &amp;gt; Y&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Neither D nor C is the eldest.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Z &amp;gt; D &amp;gt; X &amp;gt; E &amp;gt; Y &amp;gt; C&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Thus, no one is older than Z.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hence, &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;option 2&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; is the correct answer.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div&gt;The correct answer is Sport.&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Sport&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Latin is a language and fencing is a sport. So, just as Latin is a type of language, fencing is a type of sport.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Dance&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Although fencing is technically not a type of dance, some might argue that it requires grace and timing much like dance does. However, this analogy doesn&amp;#39;t hold as strongly as Fencing: Sport.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Art&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Fencing can be considered an art due to its form, precision, strategy and expressiveness - all characteristics of an artistic endeavor. However, it&amp;#39;s still primarily recognized as a sport.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Weapon&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Fencing does use weapons (&amp;eacute;p&amp;eacute;e, foil, and sabre), but this comparison is not as fitting since we&amp;#39;re looking for a category to which fencing belongs, in the same way Latin is a example of a language.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Music&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;This comparison doesn&amp;#39;t apply well since fencing is not a form of music. It&amp;#39;s a physical and tactical endeavor, not an auditory one.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

